# Changelog Template

This changelog template is designed to help software projects maintain a clear and organized record of changes, improvements, and bug fixes over time. Keeping a changelog is important because it provides transparency for users and contributors, facilitates easier troubleshooting, and helps track the evolution of the project. By documenting each change, teams can communicate updates effectively and ensure everyone is aware of the project's progress.

## Usage

- Record each significant change under the appropriate version heading.
- Include the date of release and a brief summary of the changes.
- Use consistent formatting for clarity and readability.
